article.headline: Wagner 24, Marist 14
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Matt Abbey threw two touchdown to help Wagner beat Marist 24-14 on Saturday. Abbey connected with Lou Woods for a 39-yard TD and Joe Kinard for a 29-yard score to lead the Seahawks (2-1). Abbey was 12-for-26 for 145 yards. Jason Butler rushed for 100 yards on 24 carries. Trailing 24-0, Marist (0-3) got a one-yard TD run from Ray Fiumefreddo. They closed to 24-14 with 22 seconds left on Dan Dulac's 13-yard reception from Steve McGrath. McGrath was 16-for-40 for 170 yards.
